item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Ashi:

I don’t why it would be a problem with Java if you’re running the client on the same computer you jarred it on because you would already have the correct version installed.

Sometimes when you install an older version of java first and then a newer second (without removing the old) the registry will go to the older version and not the newer. Or vice versa. I say registry because Windows has the registry and I believe that’s where the file type defaults are stored.

item.title: Webclient issue
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Unsupported Major.minor version is because the code was compiled with a higher version of java than the java that is trying to run it.
EX:

I compile my webclient with JDK 8.
You try to run it with JRE 7.
You get the Unsupported major.minor error.

Solution:
Compile the code with a lower version of JDK OR get a newer version of JRE.

JDK - Java development kit, what you use to compile.
JRE - Java Runtime environment, you can get the newest version via http://java.com
